  "lines": [
    {"number": 1, "text": "\"Nam Sibyllam quidem Cumis ego ipse oculis meis", "type": "epigraph", "section": null},
    {"number": 2, "text": "vidi in ampulla pendere, et cum illi pueri dicerent:", "type": "epigraph", "section": null},
    {"number": 3, "text": "Σίβυλλα τί θέλεις; respondebat illa: ἀποθανεῖν θέλω.\"", "type": "epigraph", "section": null},
    {"number": 4, "text": "", "type": "blank", "section": null},
    {"number": 5, "text": "       _For Ezra Pound", "type": "dedication", "section": null, "italic": true},
    {"number": 6, "text": "       il miglior fabbro_", "type": "dedication", "section": null, "italic": true},
    {"number": 7, "text": "", "type": "blank", "section": null},
    {"number": 8, "text": "", "type": "blank", "section": null},
    {"number": 9, "text": "", "type": "blank", "section": null},
    {"number": 10, "text": "", "type": "blank", "section": null},
    {"number": 11, "text": "    I. THE BURIAL OF THE DEAD", "type": "section_header", "section": "I"},
    {"number": 12, "text": "", "type": "blank", "section": "I"},
    {"number": 13, "text": "", "type": "blank", "section": "I"},
    {"number": 14, "text": "April is the cruellest month, breeding", "type": "verse", "section": "I"},
    {"number": 15, "text": "Lilacs out of the dead land, mixing", "type": "verse", "section": "I"},
    {"number": 16, "text": "Memory and desire, stirring", "type": "verse", "section": "I"},
    {"number": 17, "text": "Dull roots with spring rain.", "type": "verse", "section": "I"},
    {"number": 18, "text": "Winter kept us warm, covering", "type": "verse", "section": "I"},
    {"number": 19, "text": "Earth in forgetful snow, feeding", "type": "verse", "section": "I"},
    {"number": 20, "text": "A little life with dried tubers.", "type": "verse", "section": "I"},
    {"number": 21, "text": "Summer surprised us, coming over the Starnbergersee", "type": "verse", "section": "I"},
    {"number": 22, "text": "With a shower of rain; we stopped in the colonnade,", "type": "verse", "section": "I"},
    {"number": 23, "text": "And went on in sunlight, into the Hofgarten,", "type": "verse", "section": "I"},
    {"number": 24, "text": "And drank coffee, and talked for an hour.", "type": "verse", "section": "I"},
    {"number": 25, "text": "Bin gar keine Russin, stamm' aus Litauen, echt deutsch.", "type": "verse", "section": "I", "language": "german"},
    {"number": 26, "text": "And when we were children, staying at the archduke's,", "type": "verse", "section": "I"},
    {"number": 27, "text": "My cousin's, he took me out on a sled,", "type": "verse", "section": "I"},
    {"number": 28, "text": "And I was frightened. He said, Marie,", "type": "verse", "section": "I"},
    {"number": 29, "text": "Marie, hold on tight. And down we went.", "type": "verse", "section": "I"},
    {"number": 30, "text": "In the mountains, there you feel free.", "type": "verse", "section": "I"},
    {"number": 31, "text": "I read, much of the night, and go south in the winter.", "type": "verse", "section": "I"}
  ],
